<td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Time to turn the ole /rant on...........</span><hr size=1> K here it goes, Ill try make this short and sweet. I hope I do not piss anyone off (seems to be in my nature) but I am not holding back this time.........<br>
<br>
1) TGA, I will continue to embassodor this. As Rrawrr said, It gives smaller family like guilds the fire power of a uberguild. I moniter there channel all the time I am on, I will keep people informed of stuff as it arrises. They have no manitory raids, playing with them ect ect. Just a bunch of guilds that will help each other out if they need it. I will do all the work on this, no one else needs to worry about it.<br>
<br>
2) Raids, Officers while are encouraged to do this, are not made to do this. If you are not a officer and you would like to go raid say L Guk, ask in guild chat..you will be surprised how many people will join ya. I personally offer myself to guild each time I log in, wether it to raid, port people around, exp grind, quest, whatever. This will help us starting to get together more, and for everyone to get to know each other a lil better Get a bunch of lvl 20 and EXP grind in oasis together, what better way to meet fellow DC then to spend time with them. What if no officers are on ATM (rare yes but it happens), DC shuts down? While officers assume more responsibility on holding these, organizing ect, you as a guild member are required to carry your weight as well. If I here 1 more person whine that DC dosent get togehter anymore, and repeatly does not join us on events, talk in guild chat, stays on Annomus and reads from shadows, ect ect ect. They will be considered dead weight and droped. Now this dosent mean you have to raid with us all the time, if ever. Or you have to plan raids yourself. Just dont bitch we dont do anything and then dont contribute in any way. I personally have alot of raids planed for future, and would love people to do the same.<br>
<br>
3) Guild bank, and message boards. Will be HIGHLY encouraged to use, but hey, it is just a game, we cant force people to post here (much as Id like to). However saying that. NO ONE will be able to get anything out of guild bank unless they do post here, i dont care if you come here 1 a week, just try to come here sometimes. And offical posted raids (meaning no spur of moment, in game planed raids, which you also be seeing more of, LOL, trust me). People who posted intentions here will get pref treatment.<br>
<br>
Now for other topics discussed here..... I am WAY to hot headed to place posts here. I will surelly piss people off, and will keep it to my self. I am PISSED at certian former DC members for leaving. Not all of them, but some for sure.<br>
<br>
What DC needs is a heading to move towards so here it is. Short, sweet and simple.<br>
<br>
-We need a strong leader to head up DC, Had it, but will see if we do when the votes are in, but all that are nominated will surely be so ill say we do, but only time will tell in the end.  <br>
<br>
-Strong officer core to help him or her run it..got it.<br>
<br>
-Direction, 1) to join TGA...in works. 2) Get a strong group of people who love DC, and will stay in it thick or thin. No matter what lvl they are. Well, seems all the people using DC as a stepping stone are gone now, so we have that. Lets get this core of people we have together, get the link strong bond betwen us all, and add to it via invites and such.<br>
<br>
-Purpose. Hey its simple, we all play EQ cause its a fun game to play. So lets make it that way. You all will see that soon.<br>
<br>
I am a man of action, not words, I suck at wording stuff like this (as you can plainly see) I cant always get what I mean on paper. I will be doing alot in actions starting tonight. I hope you all join me in getting DC back to where it was, and where it should be.<br>
<br>
REMBER!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! It takes a good ass kicking to learn how to fight. We got the ass kicking, complimates of a certian few people. Not lets stand back up, lick our wounds, and get back to fighting through EQ.<br>
<br>
/rant off (really wasnt one)<br>
<br>
Biggbizz 52 Warrior<br>
Ebern 32 Wizzy<br>
